    "# 🔗 Machine Learning Based Adaptive Modulation Scheme\n",
    "**Author:** Francesco De Florence  \n",
    "**Project:** Adaptive Modulation Using Machine Learning  \n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## 📌 Project Overview\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook implements an ML-based adaptive modulation system that:\n",
    "- **Inputs:** SNR (Signal-to-Noise Ratio) and BER (Bit Error Rate)\n",
    "- **Output:** Optimal modulation scheme (BPSK / QPSK / 16-QAM / 64-QAM)\n",
    "- **Impact:** Maximises spectral efficiency while maintaining link quality\n",
    "\n",
    "### Modulation Decision Logic\n",
    "| SNR Range | Modulation | Bits/Symbol | Use Case |\n",
    "|-----------|------------|-------------|----------|\n",
    "| < 5 dB    | BPSK       | 1           | Very noisy channel |\n",
    "| 5–10 dB   | QPSK       | 2           | Moderate noise |\n",
    "| 10–20 dB  | 16-QAM     | 4           | Good channel |\n",
    "| > 20 dB   | 64-QAM     | 6           | Excellent channel |\n",
    "\n",
    "---"
   ]
  },
